comment.narrative:
1. (a) proposals and recommendations on minimum energy performance standards were introduced into the Concept of the draft Law of the Republic of Kazakhstan “On Introducing Amendments and Addenda to Some Legislative Acts of the Republic of Kazakhstan on Energy Saving and Energy Efficiency”. Approved by the Interdepartmental Commission on Legislative Activities (June 7); (b) In the comparative table of the draft Law of the Republic of Kazakhstan “On Introducing Amendments and Addenda to Some Legislative Acts of the Republic of Kazakhstan on Energy Saving and Energy Efficiency”, proposals have been made to develop Rules for establishing energy efficiency requirements for procurement of household appliances and equipment, including electrical equipment by government agencies and quasi-state sector entities, as well as on monitoring the compliance; (c) Draft standard ST RK was developed to establish energy efficiency requirements for electric motors; at the moment, it is being agreed with authorized organizations; (d) Draft Ministry Order has been prepared to establish minimum energy efficiency requirements for transformers and domestic refrigerators; the Draft Orger undergoing agreeing process;
2. As part of the interstate cooperation of testing laboratories, as well as to study requirements under the EAEU Technical Regulations, a technical training was organized in the Republic of Belarus, which was held on the basis of the Belarusian State Institute of Standardization and Certification. The training was organized for responsible experts in Kazakhstan to exchange experience and practical familiarization with the methodology and infrastructure of organizing a system for testing and certification of household appliances and equipment.
3. A test version of the web portal has been developed, with data on energy efficiency of household appliances and equipment, such as: (1) household refrigerators, washing machines, air conditioners, TVs; (2) industrial electric motors and distribution transformers. 
The following information on the above equipment will be displayed on the web portal:
- analytical data to improve energy efficiency;
- results of annual marketing and sociological researches;
- regulatory documents;
- registers of energy-efficient products;
- demonstration of various experiences from foreign countries.
The web portal is to be operated in Russian, English and Kazakh.
4. Conducted social study on consumer awareness about benefits of energy efficient appliances and equipment. Within the framework of the study:
-	2500 consumers were questioned in all regions of the country.
-	Identified awareness of energy efficiency energy saving concepts and their influence on consumer choices.
-	Prepared dynamics of changes regarding the baseline of public awareness.
5. Conducted market research of current stock and trends in sales of refrigerators, freezers and other household appliances and equipment with the focus on energy efficiency and other key factors. Within the framework of the study prepared: 
-	Detailed description of the overall structure and volume of the market of refrigerators, freezers, electric motors and transformers in Kazakhstan, with a breakdown by types and classes of energy efficiency;
-	Assesment of import/production volumes in 2016-2018 of household appliances and industrial equipment;
-	Analysis of foreign economic activity in terms of imports and exports volumes of refrigerators, freezers, electric motors and transformers, including the list of the main countries of origin/production
6. Based on last year’s experience in implementation of the pilot phase of the discount program for energy-efficient refrigerators, starting from July 1, 2019, new expanded discount program was launched in cooperation with partners represented by Operator ROP LLP, Technodom and Mechta trading houses and Bosch and LG companies. The program was to promote energy-efficient household refrigerators with ensuring waste disposal of electrical equipment in Nur-Sultan, Aktobe, Pavlodar, Karaganda and Almaty cities.Provided 2500 discount certificates to customers, each valued of 16,500 tenge, for a total amount of 41,520,000 tenge. (exchange rate 386)
7. A pilot energy audit of 15 electric motors and 15 transformers of Almaty Electric Stations JSC was conducted. This express energy audit allowed to test new point approaches in assessing the energy saving potential of electric motors and transformers relative to their baseline (energy consumption by this equipment for the full calendar year preceding the year of the express energy audit) in percentage terms. The analysis showed the energy saving potential for electric motors equal to 10%, and for the whole CHP-2, the energy saving potential can amount to 35 406 thousand kWh of electricity.
